[{"id":"cv1678","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"A scatter graph shows that as the number of hours spent playing video games increases, the test scores of students tend to decrease. What type of correlation does this describe?","o":["Positive correlation","Negative correlation","Zero correlation","Direct correlation"],"a":1,"e":"Since the test scores decrease as the gaming hours increase, the variables move in opposite directions, which is defined as a negative correlation.","d":2,"s":"9.5"},{"id":"cv1679","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"Data collected on the altitude of a mountain climber and the surrounding air temperature shows that as altitude increases, the temperature tends to fall. Identify the correlation type.","o":["Strong positive","Negative correlation","Weak positive","No correlation"],"a":1,"e":"As altitude increases, temperature decreases. This inverse relationship where one variable goes up while the other goes down is a negative correlation.","d":2,"s":"9.5"},{"id":"cv1680","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"A scientist observes that as the volume of a gas is increased at a constant temperature, the pressure of the gas decreases. What type of correlation is represented on a scatter diagram of pressure against volume?","o":["Positive correlation","Negative correlation","No correlation","Perfect positive"],"a":1,"e":"The pressure decreases as the volume increases. This trend on a scatter diagram, where variables move in opposite directions, represents a negative correlation.","d":2,"s":"9.5"},{"id":"cv1681","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"On a scatter plot, the data points are very concentrated around a straight line that slopes upwards from left to right. Which term best describes this correlation?","o":["Strong positive","Weak positive","Strong negative","Weak negative"],"a":0,"e":"The points are 'very concentrated' (strong) and the line 'slopes upwards' (positive), indicating that both variables increase together in a strong positive correlation.","d":2,"s":"9.5"},{"id":"cv1682","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"The points on a scatter diagram for height and arm span are almost in a perfect straight line going from the bottom-left to the top-right. How is this correlation described?","o":["Strong positive","Weak positive","Strong negative","No correlation"],"a":0,"e":"Because the points are 'almost in a perfect straight line', the correlation is strong. Since the line goes from 'bottom-left to top-right', it is positive as both values increase together.","d":2,"s":"9.5"},{"id":"cv1683","cat":"statistics","topic":"Scatter Diagrams","q":"A scatter graph comparing revision time and exam marks shows points that follow a very clear upward trend and are positioned very close to each other along a line. Describe this correlation.","o":["Strong positive","Weak positive","Perfect negative","Strong negative"],"a":0,"e":"The 'clear upward trend' indicates a positive correlation, and the points being 'very close to each other along a line' indicates it is strong.","d":2,"s":"9.5"}]
